  <p>Block 2 builds watershed mechanics. Students calculate <strong>water budgets</strong> for a real watershed — inputs (precipitation, inflow), storage (lakes, soil moisture), outputs (evapotranspiration, runoff, withdrawals). Distinguishes surface water from groundwater (Block 3's territory). The Cauvery watershed serves as the worked example: a single river basin shared by multiple states, with a measurable budget that no longer balances.</p>
